caption: Greek food is the BEST. Up visiting Greensboro and was craving some Tzatziki sauce. Was a bit worried when literally no one was in the place, but it’s COVID so I understand. The food did not disappoint! Was very delicious and for a good price! Will definitely come back when I want some more Gyros😁
Wonderful fresh food. Always good. Great service. What a gem.
Highly recommend the Greek salad.

Now,  I've only had their baklava cupcakes, but if their regular food is half as good as their cupcakes, is give them 10 stars.  Do not hesitate to try this place.  They're a little hidden near the ball field,  but take the time and go there.
Loved the lamb burger, Absolutely delicious!

We tried Acropolis for the first time and everything was great! The Horiatiki salad is amazing,  the Avgholemono soup is delicious and the hummus and gyros are on spot!  The location is perfect being right near Joymongers and the baseball park!

Best by far in this town. 5-6 hell 9 thumps up. Marination was insane. Yup they greek greek old school. Off the chain in flavor.

The Acropolis has been a thriving Greensboro fixture for 51 years, with dependably excellent food and service. I hadn't been there in years until yesterday, when I planned to meet my son for lunch. But I couldn't find it! Even though they …

I am a visitor to Greensboro, again, and this is my second time enjoying the Acropolis' food. Only take out now but they are putting their hearts into every order. Food was great and they added a dessert!

Great authentic Greek food! The grouper prepared mediterranean-style dish was delicious and very soft textured, because it was so fresh! It's a quiet, family owned restaurant without any annoyances ,that you would normally get at a commercial restaurant. Definitely going again soon!

Jimmy catered our son’s rehearsal dinner and knocked everyone’s socks off. We had people who said they didn’t like Greek food but once they tried it, said ‘it was effing delicious!’ The quality of the food was not notch, very generous portions and a very fair cost. We were beyond pleased and will not hesitate to use him again.

I dined there while working in Greensboro for 13 years. I loved Wednesday lunch special baked chicken, potatoes and green beans. I just learned today of Ellen’s passing. She was a dear and sweet soul. My deepest condolences to Jimmy and his sisters.

A must try in Greensboro. Family run Greek restaurant with some of the best food in the city. They have a full bar and Greek beers.  Branch out from the staple gyros and try some authentic dishes. Even the side dishes are delicious. Don't forget the dessert. Try the galactobourico.

Rice was on the mushy side, and the chicken souvlaki was smothered in seasonings.  The baklava was delicious though.  Overall, not bad.  I am not sure if everything is made fresh or if they use canned items.
Great staff and authentic food made fresh

Best gyro platter I've ever had! We also got the spinach pita pizza with white sauce and everything was made from scratch including the sauce. Delicious and generous portions.
